# Server Environment Variable Access

When writing or updating server-side code, always access environment variables through
`env` from `@/utils/env.server`.

## Required pattern

```typescript
import { env } from '@/utils/env.server';

const morphUrl = env.MORPH_URL;
```

## Avoid

- `process.env.*` directly in server routes, server actions, utilities, and services
- duplicating ad-hoc env parsing logic when `env.server.ts` already defines it

## Notes

- Client components should never import `@/utils/env.server`.
- If a needed variable is missing from `env.server.ts`, add it there first, then consume via `env`.
